461Co 1:1 Paul, called as an apostle of Christ Jesus by God's will, and our brother Sosthenes:
461Co 1:2 To God's church at Corinth, to those who are sanctified in Christ Jesus and called as saints, with all those in every place who call on the name of Jesus Christ our Lord-- theirs and ours.
461Co 1:3 Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
461Co 1:4 I always thank my God for you because of God's grace given to you in Christ Jesus,
461Co 1:5 that by Him you were made rich in everything-- in all speaking and all knowledge--
461Co 1:6 as the testimony about Christ was confirmed among you,
461Co 1:7 so that you do not lack any spiritual gift as you eagerly wait for the revelation of our Lord Jesus Christ.
461Co 1:8 He will also confirm you to the end, blameless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
461Co 1:9 God is faithful; by Him you were called into fellowship with His Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.
461Co 1:10 Now I urge you, brothers, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you all say the same thing, that there be no divisions among you, and that you be united with the same understanding and the same conviction.
461Co 1:11 For it has been reported to me about you, my brothers, by members of Chloe's household, that there are quarrels among you.
461Co 1:12 What I am saying is this: each of you says, "I'm with Paul," or "I'm with Apollos," or "I'm with Cephas," or "I'm with Christ."
461Co 1:13 Is Christ divided? Was it Paul who was crucified for you? Or were you baptized in Paul's name?
461Co 1:14 I thank God that I baptized none of you except Crispus and Gaius,
461Co 1:15 so that no one can say you had been baptized in my name.
461Co 1:16 I did, in fact, baptize the household of Stephanas; beyond that, I don't know if I baptized anyone else.
461Co 1:17 For Christ did not send me to baptize, but to preach the gospel-- not with clever words, so that the cross of Christ will not be emptied [of its effect].
461Co 1:18 For to those who are perishing the message of the cross is foolishness, but to us who are being saved it is God's power.
461Co 1:19 For it is written: I will destroy the wisdom of the wise, and I will set aside the understanding of the experts.
461Co 1:20 Where is the philosopher? Where is the scholar? Where is the debater of this age? Hasn't God made the world's wisdom foolish?
461Co 1:21 For since, in God's wisdom, the world did not know God through wisdom, God was pleased to save those who believe through the foolishness of the message preached.
461Co 1:22 For the Jews ask for signs and the Greeks seek wisdom,
461Co 1:23 but we preach Christ crucified, a stumbling block to the Jews and foolishness to the Gentiles.
461Co 1:24 Yet to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ is God's power and God's wisdom,
461Co 1:25 because God's foolishness is wiser than human wisdom, and God's weakness is stronger than human strength.
461Co 1:26 Brothers, consider your calling: not many are wise from a human perspective, not many powerful, not many of noble birth.
461Co 1:27 Instead, God has chosen the world's foolish things to shame the wise, and God has chosen the world's weak things to shame the strong.
461Co 1:28 God has chosen the world's insignificant and despised things-- the things viewed as nothing-- so He might bring to nothing the things that are viewed as something,
461Co 1:29 so that no one can boast in His presence.
461Co 1:30 But from Him you are in Christ Jesus, who for us became wisdom from God, as well as righteousness, sanctification, and redemption,
461Co 1:31 in order that, as it is written: The one who boasts must boast in the Lord.
461Co 2:1 When I came to you, brothers, announcing the testimony of God to you, I did not come with brilliance of speech or wisdom.
461Co 2:2 For I determined to know nothing among you except Jesus Christ and Him crucified.
461Co 2:3 And I was with you in weakness, in fear, and in much trembling.
461Co 2:4 My speech and my proclamation were not with persuasive words of wisdom, but with a demonstration of the Spirit and power,
461Co 2:5 so that your faith might not be based on men's wisdom but on God's power.
461Co 2:6 However, among the mature we do speak a wisdom, but not a wisdom of this age, or of the rulers of this age, who are coming to nothing.
461Co 2:7 On the contrary, we speak God's hidden wisdom in a mystery, which God predestined before the ages for our glory.
461Co 2:8 None of the rulers of this age knew it, for if they had known it, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.
461Co 2:9 But as it is written: What no eye has seen and no ear has heard, and what has never come into a man's heart, is what God has prepared for those who love Him.
461Co 2:10 Now God has revealed them to us by the Spirit, for the Spirit searches everything, even the deep things of God.
461Co 2:11 For who among men knows the concerns of a man except the spirit of the man that is in him? In the same way, no one knows the concerns of God except the Spirit of God.
461Co 2:12 Now we have not received the spirit of the world, but the Spirit who is from God, in order to know what has been freely given to us by God.
461Co 2:13 We also speak these things, not in words taught by human wisdom, but in those taught by the Spirit, explaining spiritual things to spiritual people.
461Co 2:14 But the natural man does not welcome what comes from God's Spirit, because it is foolishness to him; he is not able to know it since it is evaluated spiritually.
461Co 2:15 The spiritual person, however, can evaluate everything, yet he himself cannot be evaluated by anyone.
461Co 2:16 For: who has known the Lord's mind, that he may instruct Him? But we have the mind of Christ.
461Co 3:1 Brothers, I was not able to speak to you as spiritual people but as people of the flesh, as babies in Christ.
461Co 3:2 I fed you milk, not solid food, because you were not yet able to receive it. In fact, you are still not able,
461Co 3:3 because you are still fleshly. For since there is envy and strife among you, are you not fleshly and living like ordinary people?
461Co 3:4 For whenever someone says, "I'm with Paul," and another, "I'm with Apollos," are you not [typical] men?
461Co 3:5 So, what is Apollos? And what is Paul? They are servants through whom you believed, and each has the role the Lord has given.
461Co 3:6 I planted, Apollos watered, but God gave the growth.
461Co 3:7 So then neither the one who plants nor the one who waters is anything, but only God who gives the growth.
461Co 3:8 Now the one who plants and the one who waters are equal, and each will receive his own reward according to his own labor.
461Co 3:9 For we are God's co-workers. You are God's field, God's building.
461Co 3:10 According to God's grace that was given to me, as a skilled master builder I have laid a foundation, and another builds on it. But each one must be careful how he builds on it,
461Co 3:11 because no one can lay any other foundation than what has been laid-- that is, Jesus Christ.
461Co 3:12 If anyone builds on the foundation with gold, silver, costly stones, wood, hay, or straw,
461Co 3:13 each one's work will become obvious, for the day will disclose it, because it will be revealed by fire; the fire will test the quality of each one's work.
461Co 3:14 If anyone's work that he has built survives, he will receive a reward.
461Co 3:15 If anyone's work is burned up, it will be lost, but he will be saved; yet it will be like an escape through fire.
461Co 3:16 Don't you know that you are God's sanctuary and that the Spirit of God lives in you?
461Co 3:17 If anyone ruins God's sanctuary, God will ruin him; for God's sanctuary is holy, and that is what you are.
461Co 3:18 No one should deceive himself. If anyone among you thinks he is wise in this age, he must become foolish so that he can become wise.
461Co 3:19 For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God, since it is written: He catches the wise in their craftiness--
461Co 3:20 and again, The Lord knows the reasonings of the wise, that they are futile.
461Co 3:21 So no one should boast in men, for all things are yours:
461Co 3:22 whether Paul or Apollos or Cephas or the world or life or death or things present or things to come-- all are yours,
461Co 3:23 and you belong to Christ, and Christ to God.
461Co 4:1 A person should consider us in this way: as servants of Christ and managers of God's mysteries.
461Co 4:2 In this regard, it is expected of managers that each one be found faithful.
461Co 4:3 It is of little importance that I should be evaluated by you or by a human court. In fact, I don't even evaluate myself.
461Co 4:4 For I am not conscious of anything against myself, but I am not justified by this. The One who evaluates me is the Lord.
461Co 4:5 Therefore don't judge anything prematurely, before the Lord comes, who will both bring to light what is hidden in darkness and reveal the intentions of the hearts. And then praise will come to each one from God.
461Co 4:6 Now, brothers, I have applied these things to myself and Apollos for your benefit, so that you may learn from us the saying: "Nothing beyond what is written." The purpose is that none of you will be inflated with pride in favor of one person over another.
461Co 4:7 For who makes you so superior? What do you have that you didn't receive? If, in fact, you did receive it, why do you boast as if you hadn't received it?
461Co 4:8 Already you are full! Already you are rich! You have begun to reign as kings without us-- and I wish you did reign, so that we also could reign with you!
461Co 4:9 For I think God has displayed us, the apostles, in last place, like men condemned to die: we have become a spectacle to the world and to angels and to men.
461Co 4:10 We are fools for Christ, but you are wise in Christ! We are weak, but you are strong! You are distinguished, but we are dishonored!
461Co 4:11 Up to the present hour we are both hungry and thirsty; we are poorly clothed, roughly treated, homeless;
461Co 4:12 we labor, working with our own hands. When we are reviled, we bless; when we are persecuted, we endure it;
461Co 4:13 when we are slandered, we entreat. We are, even now, like the world's garbage, like the filth of all things.
461Co 4:14 I'm not writing this to shame you, but to warn you as my dear children.
461Co 4:15 For you can have 10,000 instructors in Christ, but you can't have many fathers. Now I have fathered you in Christ Jesus through the gospel.
461Co 4:16 Therefore I urge you, be imitators of me.
461Co 4:17 This is why I have sent to you Timothy, who is my beloved and faithful child in the Lord. He will remind you about my ways in Christ Jesus, just as I teach everywhere in every church.
461Co 4:18 Now some are inflated with pride, as though I were not coming to you.
461Co 4:19 But I will come to you soon, if the Lord wills, and I will know not the talk but the power of those who are inflated with pride.
461Co 4:20 For the kingdom of God is not in talk but in power.
461Co 4:21 What do you want? Should I come to you with a rod, or in love and a spirit of gentleness?
461Co 5:1 It is widely reported that there is sexual immorality among you, and the kind of sexual immorality that is not even condoned among the Gentiles-- a man is living with his father's wife.
461Co 5:2 And you are inflated with pride, instead of filled with grief so that he who has committed this act might be removed from among you.
461Co 5:3 For though absent in body but present in spirit, I have already decided about him who has done this thing as though I were present.
461Co 5:4 In the name of our Lord Jesus, when you are assembled, along with my spirit and with the power of our Lord Jesus,
461Co 5:5 turn that one over to Satan for the destruction of the flesh, so that his spirit may be saved in the Day of the Lord.
461Co 5:6 Your boasting is not good. Don't you know that a little yeast permeates the whole batch of dough?
461Co 5:7 Clean out the old yeast so that you may be a new batch, since you are unleavened. For Christ our Passover has been sacrificed.
461Co 5:8 Therefore, let us observe the feast, not with old yeast, or with the yeast of malice and evil, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.
461Co 5:9 I wrote to you in a letter not to associate with sexually immoral people--
461Co 5:10 by no means referring to this world's immoral people, or to the greedy and swindlers, or to idolaters; otherwise you would have to leave the world.
461Co 5:11 But now I am writing you not to associate with anyone who bears the name of brother who is sexually immoral or greedy, an idolater or a reviler, a drunkard or a swindler. Do not even eat with such a person.
461Co 5:12 For what is it to me to judge outsiders? Do you not judge those who are inside?
461Co 5:13 But God judges outsiders. Put away the evil person from among yourselves.
461Co 6:1 Does any of you who has a complaint against someone dare go to law before the unrighteous, and not before the saints?
461Co 6:2 Or do you not know that the saints will judge the world? And if the world is judged by you, are you unworthy to judge the smallest cases?
461Co 6:3 Do you not know that we will judge angels-- not to speak of things pertaining to this life?
461Co 6:4 So if you have cases pertaining to this life, do you select those who have no standing in the church to judge?
461Co 6:5 I say this to your shame! Can it be that there is not one wise person among you who will be able to arbitrate between his brothers?
461Co 6:6 Instead, brother goes to law against brother, and that before unbelievers!
461Co 6:7 Therefore, it is already a total defeat for you that you have lawsuits against one another. Why not rather put up with injustice? Why not rather be cheated?
461Co 6:8 Instead, you act unjustly and cheat-- and this to brothers!
461Co 6:9 Do you not know that the unjust will not inherit God's kingdom? Do not be deceived: no sexually immoral people, idolaters, adulterers, male prostitutes, homosexuals,
461Co 6:10 thieves, greedy people, drunkards, revilers, or swindlers will inherit God's kingdom.
461Co 6:11 Some of you were like this; but you were washed, you were sanctified, you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ and by the Spirit of our God.
461Co 6:12 "Everything is permissible for me," but not everything is helpful. "Everything is permissible for me," but I will not be brought under the control of anything.
461Co 6:13 "Foods for the stomach and the stomach for foods," but God will do away with both of them. The body is not for sexual immorality but for the Lord, and the Lord for the body.
461Co 6:14 God raised up the Lord and will also raise us up by His power.
461Co 6:15 Do you not know that your bodies are the members of Christ? So should I take the members of Christ and make them members of a prostitute? Absolutely not!
461Co 6:16 Do you not know that anyone joined to a prostitute is one body with her? For it says, The two will become one flesh.
461Co 6:17 But anyone joined to the Lord is one spirit with Him.
461Co 6:18 Flee from sexual immorality! "Every sin a person can commit is outside the body," but the person who is sexually immoral sins against his own body.
461Co 6:19 Do you not know that your body is a sanctuary of the Holy Spirit who is in you, whom you have from God? You are not your own,
461Co 6:20 for you were bought at a price; therefore glorify God in your body.
461Co 7:1 About the things you wrote: "It is good for a man not to have relations with a woman."
461Co 7:2 But because of sexual immorality, each man should have his own wife, and each woman should have her own husband.
461Co 7:3 A husband should fulfill his marital duty to his wife, and likewise a wife to her husband.
461Co 7:4 A wife does not have authority over her own body, but her husband does. Equally, a husband does not have authority over his own body, but his wife does.
461Co 7:5 Do not deprive one another-- except when you agree, for a time, to devote yourselves to prayer. Then come together again; otherwise, Satan may tempt you because of your lack of self-control.
461Co 7:6 I say this as a concession, not as a command.
461Co 7:7 I wish that all people were just like me. But each has his own gift from God, one this and another that.
461Co 7:8 I say to the unmarried and to widows: It is good for them if they remain as I am.
461Co 7:9 But if they do not have self-control, they should marry, for it is better to marry than to burn with desire.
461Co 7:10 I command the married-- not I, but the Lord-- a wife is not to leave her husband.
461Co 7:11 But if she does leave, she must remain unmarried or be reconciled to her husband-- and a husband is not to leave his wife.
461Co 7:12 But to the rest I, not the Lord, say: If any brother has an unbelieving wife, and she is willing to live with him, he must not leave her.
461Co 7:13 Also, if any woman has an unbelieving husband, and he is willing to live with her, she must not leave her husband.
461Co 7:14 For the unbelieving husband is sanctified by the wife, and the unbelieving wife is sanctified by the Christian husband. Otherwise your children would be unclean, but now they are holy.
461Co 7:15 But if the unbeliever leaves, let him leave. A brother or a sister is not bound in such cases. God has called you to peace.
461Co 7:16 For you, wife, how do you know whether you will save your husband? Or you, husband, how do you know whether you will save your wife?
461Co 7:17 However, each one must live his life in the situation the Lord assigned when God called him. This is what I command in all the churches.
461Co 7:18 Was anyone already circumcised when he was called? He should not undo his circumcision. Was anyone called while uncircumcised? He should not get circumcised.
461Co 7:19 Circumcision does not matter and uncircumcision does not matter, but keeping God's commandments does.
461Co 7:20 Each person should remain in the life situation in which he was called.
461Co 7:21 Were you called while a slave? It should not be a concern to you. But if you can become free, by all means take the opportunity.
461Co 7:22 For he who is called by the Lord as a slave is the Lord's freedman. Likewise he who is called as a free man is Christ's slave.
461Co 7:23 You were bought at a price; do not become slaves of men.
461Co 7:24 Brothers, each person should remain with God in whatever situation he was called.
461Co 7:25 About virgins: I have no command from the Lord, but I do give an opinion as one who by the Lord's mercy is trustworthy.
461Co 7:26 Therefore I consider this to be good because of the present distress: it is fine for a man to stay as he is.
461Co 7:27 Are you bound to a wife? Do not seek to be loosed. Are you loosed from a wife? Do not seek a wife.
461Co 7:28 However, if you do get married, you have not sinned, and if a virgin marries, she has not sinned. But such people will have trouble in this life, and I am trying to spare you.
461Co 7:29 And I say this, brothers: the time is limited, so from now on those who have wives should be as though they had none,
461Co 7:30 those who weep as though they did not weep, those who rejoice as though they did not rejoice, those who buy as though they did not possess,
461Co 7:31 and those who use the world as though they did not make full use of it. For this world in its current form is passing away.
461Co 7:32 I want you to be without concerns. An unmarried man is concerned about the things of the Lord-- how he may please the Lord.
461Co 7:33 But a married man is concerned about the things of the world-- how he may please his wife--
461Co 7:34 and he is divided. An unmarried woman or a virgin is concerned about the things of the Lord, so that she may be holy both in body and in spirit. But a married woman is concerned about the things of the world-- how she may please her husband.
461Co 7:35 Now I am saying this for your own benefit, not to put a restraint on you, but because of what is proper, and so that you may be devoted to the Lord without distraction.
461Co 7:36 But if any man thinks he is acting improperly toward his virgin, if she is past marriageable age, and so it must be, he can do what he wants. He is not sinning; they can get married.
461Co 7:37 But he who stands firm in his heart (who is under no compulsion, but has control over his own will) and has decided in his heart to keep his own virgin, will do well.
461Co 7:38 So then he who marries his virgin does well, but he who does not marry will do better.
461Co 7:39 A wife is bound as long as her husband is living. But if her husband dies, she is free to be married to anyone she wants-- only in the Lord.
461Co 7:40 But she is happier if she remains as she is, in my opinion. And I think that I also have the Spirit of God.
461Co 8:1 About food offered to idols: We know that "we all have knowledge." Knowledge inflates with pride, but love builds up.
461Co 8:2 If anyone thinks he knows anything, he does not yet know it as he ought to know it.
461Co 8:3 But if anyone loves God, he is known by Him.
461Co 8:4 About eating food offered to idols, then, we know that "an idol is nothing in the world," and that "there is no God but one."
461Co 8:5 For even if there are so-called gods, whether in heaven or on earth-- as there are many "gods" and many "lords"--
461Co 8:6 yet for us there is one God, the Father, from whom are all things, and we for Him; and one Lord, Jesus Christ, through whom are all things, and we through Him.
461Co 8:7 However, not everyone has this knowledge. In fact, some have been so used to idolatry up until now, that when they eat food offered to an idol, their conscience, being weak, is defiled.
461Co 8:8 Food will not make us acceptable to God. We are not inferior if we don't eat, and we are not better if we do eat.
461Co 8:9 But be careful that this right of yours in no way becomes a stumbling block to the weak.
461Co 8:10 For if somebody sees you, the one who has this knowledge, dining in an idol's temple, won't his weak conscience be encouraged to eat food offered to idols?
461Co 8:11 Then the weak person, the brother for whom Christ died, is ruined by your knowledge.
461Co 8:12 Now when you sin like this against the brothers and wound their weak conscience, you are sinning against Christ.
461Co 8:13 Therefore, if food causes my brother to fall, I will never again eat meat, so that I won't cause my brother to fall.
461Co 9:1 Am I not free? Am I not an apostle? Have I not seen Jesus our Lord? Are you not my work in the Lord?
461Co 9:2 If I am not an apostle to others, at least I am to you, for you are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord.
461Co 9:3 My defense to those who examine me is this:
461Co 9:4 Don't we have the right to eat and drink?
461Co 9:5 Don't we have the right to be accompanied by a Christian wife, like the other apostles, the Lord's brothers, and Cephas?
461Co 9:6 Or is it only Barnabas and I who have no right to refrain from working?
461Co 9:7 Who ever goes to war at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat its fruit? Or who shepherds a flock and does not drink the milk from the flock?
461Co 9:8 Am I saying this from a human perspective? Doesn't the law also say the same thing?
461Co 9:9 For it is written in the law of Moses, Do not muzzle an ox while it treads out the grain. Is God really concerned with oxen?
461Co 9:10 Or isn't He really saying it for us? Yes, this is written for us, because he who plows ought to plow in hope, and he who threshes should do so in hope of sharing the crop.
461Co 9:11 If we have sown spiritual things for you, is it too much if we reap material things from you?
461Co 9:12 If others share this authority over you, don't we even more? However, we have not used this authority; instead we endure everything so that we will not hinder the gospel of Christ.
461Co 9:13 Do you not know that those who perform the temple services eat the food from the temple, and those who serve at the altar share in the offerings of the altar?
461Co 9:14 In the same way, the Lord has commanded that those who preach the gospel should earn their living by the gospel.
461Co 9:15 But I have used none of these rights, and I have not written this to make it happen that way for me. For it would be better for me to die than for anyone to deprive me of my boast!
461Co 9:16 For if I preach the gospel, I have no reason to boast, because an obligation is placed on me. And woe to me if I do not preach the gospel!
461Co 9:17 For if I do this willingly, I have a reward; but if unwillingly, I am entrusted with a stewardship.
461Co 9:18 What then is my reward? To preach the gospel and offer it free of charge, and not make full use of my authority in the gospel.
461Co 9:19 For although I am free from all people, I have made myself a slave to all, in order to win more people.
461Co 9:20 To the Jews I became like a Jew, to win Jews; to those under the law, like one under the law-- though I myself am not under the law-- to win those under the law.
461Co 9:21 To those who are outside the law, like one outside the law-- not being outside God's law, but under the law of Christ-- to win those outside the law.
461Co 9:22 To the weak I became weak, in order to win the weak. I have become all things to all people, so that I may by all means save some.
461Co 9:23 Now I do all this because of the gospel, that I may become a partner in its benefits.
461Co 9:24 Do you not know that the runners in a stadium all race, but only one receives the prize? Run in such a way that you may win.
461Co 9:25 Now everyone who competes exercises self-control in everything. However, they do it to receive a perishable crown, but we an imperishable one.
461Co 9:26 Therefore I do not run like one who runs aimlessly, or box like one who beats the air.
461Co 9:27 Instead, I discipline my body and bring it under strict control, so that after preaching to others, I myself will not be disqualified.
461Co 10:1 Now I want you to know, brothers, that our fathers were all under the cloud, all passed through the sea,
461Co 10:2 and all were baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea.
461Co 10:3 They all ate the same spiritual food,
461Co 10:4 and all drank the same spiritual drink. For they drank from a spiritual rock that followed them, and that rock was Christ.
461Co 10:5 But God was not pleased with most of them, for they were struck down in the desert.
461Co 10:6 Now these things became examples for us, so that we will not desire evil as they did.
461Co 10:7 Don't become idolaters as some of them were; as it is written, The people sat down to eat and drink, and got up to play.
461Co 10:8 Let us not commit sexual immorality as some of them did, and in a single day 23,000 people fell dead.
461Co 10:9 Let us not tempt Christ as some of them did, and were destroyed by snakes.
461Co 10:10 Nor should we complain as some of them did, and were killed by the destroyer.
461Co 10:11 Now these things happened to them as examples, and they were written as a warning to us, on whom the ends of the ages have come.
461Co 10:12 Therefore, whoever thinks he stands must be careful not to fall!
461Co 10:13 No temptation has overtaken you except what is common to humanity. God is faithful and He will not allow you to be tempted beyond what you are able, but with the temptation He will also provide a way of escape, so that you are able to bear it.
461Co 10:14 Therefore, my dear friends, flee from idolatry.
461Co 10:15 I am speaking as to wise people. Judge for yourselves what I say.
461Co 10:16 The cup of blessing that we bless, is it not a sharing in the blood of Christ? The bread that we break, is it not a sharing in the body of Christ?
461Co 10:17 Because there is one bread, we who are many are one body, for all of us share that one bread.
461Co 10:18 Look at the people of Israel. Are not those who eat the sacrifices partners in the altar?
461Co 10:19 What am I saying then? That food offered to idols is anything, or that an idol is anything?
461Co 10:20 No, but I do say that what they sacrifice, they sacrifice to demons and not to God. I do not want you to be partners with demons!
461Co 10:21 You cannot drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You cannot share in the Lord's table and the table of demons.
461Co 10:22 Or are we provoking the Lord to jealousy? Are we stronger than He?
461Co 10:23 "Everything is permissible," but not everything is helpful. "Everything is permissible," but not everything builds up.
461Co 10:24 No one should seek his own [good], but [the good] of the other person.
461Co 10:25 Eat everything that is sold in the meat market, asking no questions for conscience' sake, for
461Co 10:26 the earth is the Lord's, and all that is in it.
461Co 10:27 If one of the unbelievers invites you over and you want to go, eat everything that is set before you, without raising questions of conscience.
461Co 10:28 But if someone says to you, "This is food offered to an idol," do not eat it, out of consideration for the one who told you, and for conscience' sake.
461Co 10:29 I do not mean your own conscience, but the other person's. For why is my freedom judged by another person's conscience?
461Co 10:30 If I partake with thanks, why am I slandered because of something for which I give thanks?
461Co 10:31 Therefore, whether you eat or drink, or whatever you do, do everything for God's glory.
461Co 10:32 Give no offense to the Jews or the Greeks or the church of God,
461Co 10:33 just as I also try to please all people in all things, not seeking my own profit, but the profit of many, that they may be saved.
461Co 11:1 Be imitators of me, as I also am of Christ.
461Co 11:2 Now I praise you because you remember me in all things and keep the traditions just as I delivered them to you.
461Co 11:3 But I want you to know that Christ is the head of every man, and the man is the head of the woman, and God is the head of Christ.
461Co 11:4 Every man who prays or prophesies with something on his head dishonors his head.
461Co 11:5 But every woman who prays or prophesies with her head uncovered dishonors her head, since that is one and the same as having her head shaved.
461Co 11:6 So if a woman's head is not covered, her hair should be cut off. But if it is disgraceful for a woman to have her hair cut off or her head shaved, she should be covered.
461Co 11:7 A man, in fact, should not cover his head, because he is God's image and glory, but woman is man's glory.
461Co 11:8 For man did not come from woman, but woman came from man;
461Co 11:9 and man was not created for woman, but woman for man.
461Co 11:10 This is why a woman should have [a symbol of] authority on her head: because of the angels.
461Co 11:11 However, in the Lord, woman is not independent of man, and man is not independent of woman.
461Co 11:12 For just as woman came from man, so man comes through woman, and all things come from God.
461Co 11:13 Judge for yourselves: Is it proper for a woman to pray to God with her head uncovered?
461Co 11:14 Does not even nature itself teach you that if a man has long hair it is a disgrace to him,
461Co 11:15 but that if a woman has long hair, it is her glory? For her hair is given to her as a covering.
461Co 11:16 But if anyone wants to argue about this, we have no other custom, nor do the churches of God.
461Co 11:17 Now in giving the following instruction I do not praise you, since you come together not for the better but for the worse.
461Co 11:18 For, to begin with, I hear that when you come together as a church there are divisions among you, and in part I believe it.
461Co 11:19 There must, indeed, be factions among you, so that the approved among you may be recognized.
461Co 11:20 Therefore when you come together in one place, it is not really to eat the Lord's Supper.
461Co 11:21 For in eating, each one takes his own supper ahead of others, and one person is hungry while another is drunk!
461Co 11:22 Don't you have houses to eat and drink in? Or do you look down on the church of God and embarrass those who have nothing? What should I say to you? Should I praise you? I do not praise you for this!
461Co 11:23 For I received from the Lord what I also passed on to you: on the night when He was betrayed, the Lord Jesus took bread,
461Co 11:24 gave thanks, broke it, and said, "This is My body, which is for you. Do this in remembrance of Me."
461Co 11:25 In the same way [He] also [took] the cup, after supper, and said, "This cup is the new covenant in My blood. Do this, as often as you drink it, in remembrance of Me."
461Co 11:26 For as often as you eat this bread and drink the cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until He comes.
461Co 11:27 Therefore, whoever eats the bread or drinks the cup of the Lord in an unworthy way will be guilty of sin against the body and blood of the Lord.
461Co 11:28 So a man should examine himself; in this way he should eat of the bread and drink of the cup.
461Co 11:29 For whoever eats and drinks without recognizing the body, eats and drinks judgment on himself.
461Co 11:30 This is why many are sick and ill among you, and many have fallen asleep.
461Co 11:31 If we were properly evaluating ourselves, we would not be judged,
461Co 11:32 but when we are judged, we are disciplined by the Lord, so that we may not be condemned with the world.
461Co 11:33 Therefore, my brothers, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.
461Co 11:34 If anyone is hungry, he should eat at home, so that you can come together and not cause judgment. And I will give instructions about the other matters whenever I come.
461Co 12:1 About matters of the spirit: brothers, I do not want you to be unaware.
461Co 12:2 You know how, when you were pagans, you were led to dumb idols-- being led astray.
461Co 12:3 Therefore I am informing you that no one speaking by the Spirit of God says, "Jesus is cursed," and no one can say, "Jesus is Lord," except by the Holy Spirit.
461Co 12:4 Now there are different gifts, but the same Spirit.
461Co 12:5 There are different ministries, but the same Lord.
461Co 12:6 And there are different activities, but the same God is active in everyone and everything.
461Co 12:7 A manifestation of the Spirit is given to each person to produce what is beneficial:
461Co 12:8 to one is given a message of wisdom through the Spirit, to another, a message of knowledge by the same Spirit,
461Co 12:9 to another, faith by the same Spirit, to another, gifts of healing by the one Spirit,
461Co 12:10 to another, the performing of miracles, to another, prophecy, to another, distinguishing between spirits, to another, different kinds of languages, to another, interpretation of languages.
461Co 12:11 But one and the same Spirit is active in all these, distributing to each one as He wills.
461Co 12:12 For as the body is one and has many parts, and all the parts of that body, though many, are one body-- so also is Christ.
461Co 12:13 For we were all baptized by one Spirit into one body-- whether Jews or Greeks, whether slaves or free-- and we were all made to drink of one Spirit.
461Co 12:14 So the body is not one part but many.
461Co 12:15 If the foot should say, "Because I'm not a hand, I don't belong to the body," in spite of this it still belongs to the body.
461Co 12:16 And if the ear should say, "Because I'm not an eye, I don't belong to the body," in spite of this it still belongs to the body.
461Co 12:17 If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole were an ear, where would be the sense of smell?
461Co 12:18 But now God has placed the parts, each one of them, in the body just as He wanted.
461Co 12:19 And if they were all the same part, where would the body be?
461Co 12:20 Now there are many parts, yet one body.
461Co 12:21 So the eye cannot say to the hand, "I don't need you!" nor again the head to the feet, "I don't need you!"
461Co 12:22 On the contrary, all the more, those parts of the body that seem to be weaker are necessary.
461Co 12:23 And those parts of the body that we think to be less honorable, we clothe these with greater honor, and our unpresentable parts have a better presentation.
461Co 12:24 But our presentable parts have no need [of clothing]. Instead, God has put the body together, giving greater honor to the less honorable,
461Co 12:25 so that there would be no division in the body, but that the members would have the same concern for each other.
461Co 12:26 So if one member suffers, all the members suffer with it; if one member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.
461Co 12:27 Now you are the body of Christ, and individual members of it.
461Co 12:28 And God has placed these in the church: first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, next, miracles, then gifts of healing, helping, managing, various kinds of languages.
461Co 12:29 Are all apostles? Are all prophets? Are all teachers? Do all do miracles?
461Co 12:30 Do all have gifts of healing? Do all speak in languages? Do all interpret?
461Co 12:31 But desire the greater gifts. And I will show you an even better way.
461Co 13:1 If I speak the languages of men and of angels, but do not have love, I am a sounding gong or a clanging cymbal.
461Co 13:2 If I have [the gift of] prophecy, and understand all mysteries and all knowledge, and if I have all faith, so that I can move mountains, but do not have love, I am nothing.
461Co 13:3 And if I donate all my goods to feed the poor, and if I give my body to be burned, but do not have love, I gain nothing.
461Co 13:4 Love is patient; love is kind. Love does not envy; is not boastful; is not conceited;
461Co 13:5 does not act improperly; is not selfish; is not provoked; does not keep a record of wrongs;
461Co 13:6 finds no joy in unrighteousness, but rejoices in the truth;
461Co 13:7 bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.
461Co 13:8 Love never ends. But as for prophecies, they will come to an end; as for languages, they will cease; as for knowledge, it will come to an end.
461Co 13:9 For we know in part, and we prophesy in part.
461Co 13:10 But when the perfect comes, the partial will come to an end.
461Co 13:11 When I was a child, I spoke like a child, I thought like a child, I reasoned like a child. When I became a man, I put aside childish things.
461Co 13:12 For now we see indistinctly, as in a mirror, but then face to face. Now I know in part, but then I will know fully, as I am fully known.
461Co 13:13 Now these three remain: faith, hope, and love. But the greatest of these is love.
461Co 14:1 Pursue love and desire spiritual gifts, and above all that you may prophesy.
461Co 14:2 For the person who speaks in [another] language is not speaking to men but to God, since no one understands him; however, he speaks mysteries in the Spirit.
461Co 14:3 But the person who prophesies speaks to people for edification, encouragement, and consolation.
461Co 14:4 The person who speaks in [another] language builds himself up, but he who prophesies builds up the church.
461Co 14:5 I wish all of you spoke in other languages, but even more that you prophesied. The person who prophesies is greater than the person who speaks in languages, unless he interprets so that the church may be built up.
461Co 14:6 But now, brothers, if I come to you speaking in [other] languages, how will I benefit you unless I speak to you with a revelation or knowledge or prophecy or teaching?
461Co 14:7 Even inanimate things producing sounds-- whether flute or harp-- if they don't make a distinction in the notes, how will what is played on the flute or harp be recognized?
461Co 14:8 In fact, if the trumpet makes an unclear sound, who will prepare for battle?
461Co 14:9 In the same way, unless you use your tongue for intelligible speech, how will what is spoken be known? For you will be speaking into the air.
461Co 14:10 There are doubtless many different kinds of languages in the world, and all have meaning.
461Co 14:11 Therefore, if I do not know the meaning of the language, I will be a foreigner to the speaker, and the speaker will be a foreigner to me.
461Co 14:12 So also you-- since you are zealous in matters of the spirit, seek to excel in building up the church.
461Co 14:13 Therefore the person who speaks in [another] language should pray that he can interpret.
461Co 14:14 For if I pray in [another] language, my spirit prays, but my understanding is unfruitful.
461Co 14:15 What then? I will pray with the spirit, and I will also pray with my understanding. I will sing with the spirit, and I will also sing with my understanding.
461Co 14:16 Otherwise, if you bless with the spirit, how will the uninformed person say "Amen" at your giving of thanks, since he does not know what you are saying?
461Co 14:17 For you may very well be giving thanks, but the other person is not being built up.
461Co 14:18 I thank God that I speak in [other] languages more than all of you;
461Co 14:19 yet in the church I would rather speak five words with my understanding, in order to teach others also, than 10,000 words in [another] language.
461Co 14:20 Brothers, don't be childish in your thinking, but be infants in evil and adult in your thinking.
461Co 14:21 It is written in the law: By people of other languages and by the lips of foreigners, I will speak to this people; and even then, they will not listen to Me, says the Lord.
461Co 14:22 It follows that speaking in other languages is intended as a sign, not to believers but to unbelievers. But prophecy is not for unbelievers but for believers.
461Co 14:23 Therefore if the whole church assembles together, and all are speaking in [other] languages, and people who are uninformed or unbelievers come in, will they not say that you are out of your minds?
461Co 14:24 But if all are prophesying, and some unbeliever or uninformed person comes in, he is convicted by all and is judged by all.
461Co 14:25 The secrets of his heart will be revealed, and as a result he will fall down on his face and worship God, proclaiming, "God is really among you."
461Co 14:26 How is it then, brothers? Whenever you come together, each one has a psalm, a teaching, a revelation, [another] language, or an interpretation. All things must be done for edification.
461Co 14:27 If any person speaks in [another] language, there should be only two, or at the most three, each in turn, and someone must interpret.
461Co 14:28 But if there is no interpreter, that person should keep silent in the church and speak to himself and to God.
461Co 14:29 Two or three prophets should speak, and the others should evaluate.
461Co 14:30 But if something has been revealed to another person sitting there, the first prophet should be silent.
461Co 14:31 For you can all prophesy one by one, so that everyone may learn and everyone may be encouraged.
461Co 14:32 And the prophets' spirits are under the control of the prophets,
461Co 14:33 since God is not a God of disorder but of peace. As in all the churches of the saints,
461Co 14:34 the women should be silent in the churches, for they are not permitted to speak, but should be submissive, as the law also says.
461Co 14:35 And if they want to learn something, they should ask their own husbands at home, for it is disgraceful for a woman to speak in the church meeting.
461Co 14:36 Did the word of God originate from you, or did it come to you only?
461Co 14:37 If anyone thinks he is a prophet or spiritual, he should recognize that what I write to you is the Lord's command.
461Co 14:38 But if anyone ignores this, he will be ignored.
461Co 14:39 Therefore, my brothers, be eager to prophesy, and do not forbid speaking in [other] languages.
461Co 14:40 But everything must be done decently and in order.
461Co 15:1 Now brothers, I want to clarify for you the gospel I proclaimed to you; you received it and have taken your stand on it.
461Co 15:2 You are also saved by it, if you hold to the message I proclaimed to you-- unless you believed to no purpose.
461Co 15:3 For I passed on to you as most important what I also received: that Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures,
461Co 15:4 that He was buried, that He was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures,
461Co 15:5 and that He appeared to Cephas, then to the Twelve.
461Co 15:6 Then He appeared to over 500 brothers at one time, most of whom remain to the present, but some have fallen asleep.
461Co 15:7 Then He appeared to James, then to all the apostles.
461Co 15:8 Last of all, as to one abnormally born, He also appeared to me.
461Co 15:9 For I am the least of the apostles, unworthy to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.
461Co 15:10 But by God's grace I am what I am, and His grace toward me was not ineffective. However, I worked more than any of them, yet not I, but God's grace that was with me.
461Co 15:11 Therefore, whether it is I or they, so we preach and so you have believed.
461Co 15:12 Now if Christ is preached as raised from the dead, how can some of you say, "There is no resurrection of the dead"?
461Co 15:13 But if there is no resurrection of the dead, then Christ has not been raised;
461Co 15:14 and if Christ has not been raised, then our preaching is without foundation, and so is your faith.
461Co 15:15 In addition, we are found to be false witnesses about God, because we have testified about God that He raised up Christ-- whom He did not raise up if in fact the dead are not raised.
461Co 15:16 For if the dead are not raised, Christ has not been raised.
461Co 15:17 And if Christ has not been raised, your faith is worthless; you are still in your sins.
461Co 15:18 Therefore those who have fallen asleep in Christ have also perished.
461Co 15:19 If we have placed our hope in Christ for this life only, we should be pitied more than anyone.
461Co 15:20 But now Christ has been raised from the dead, the firstfruits of those who have fallen asleep.
461Co 15:21 For since death came through a man, the resurrection of the dead also comes through a man.
461Co 15:22 For just as in Adam all die, so also in Christ all will be made alive.
461Co 15:23 But each in his own order: Christ, the firstfruits; afterward, at His coming, the people of Christ.
461Co 15:24 Then comes the end, when He hands over the kingdom to God the Father, when He abolishes all rule and all authority and power.
461Co 15:25 For He must reign until He puts all His enemies under His feet.
461Co 15:26 The last enemy to be abolished is death.
461Co 15:27 For He has put everything under His feet. But when it says "everything" is put under Him, it is obvious that He who puts everything under Him is the exception.
461Co 15:28 And when everything is subject to Him, then the Son Himself will also be subject to Him who subjected everything to Him, so that God may be all in all.
461Co 15:29 Otherwise what will they do who are being baptized for the dead? If the dead are not raised at all, then why are people baptized for them?
461Co 15:30 Why are we in danger every hour?
461Co 15:31 I affirm by the pride in you that I have in Christ Jesus our Lord: I die every day!
461Co 15:32 If I fought wild animals in Ephesus with only human hope, what good does that do me? If the dead are not raised, Let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die.
461Co 15:33 Do not be deceived: "Bad company corrupts good morals."
461Co 15:34 Become right-minded and stop sinning, because some people are ignorant about God. I say this to your shame.
461Co 15:35 But someone will say, "How are the dead raised? What kind of body will they have when they come?"
461Co 15:36 Foolish one! What you sow does not come to life unless it dies.
461Co 15:37 And as for what you sow-- you are not sowing the future body, but only a seed, perhaps of wheat or another grain.
461Co 15:38 But God gives it a body as He wants, and to each of the seeds its own body.
461Co 15:39 Not all flesh is the same flesh; there is one flesh for humans, another for animals, another for birds, and another for fish.
461Co 15:40 There are heavenly bodies and earthly bodies, but the splendor of the heavenly bodies is different from that of the earthly ones.
461Co 15:41 There is a splendor of the sun, another of the moon, and another of the stars; for star differs from star in splendor.
461Co 15:42 So it is with the resurrection of the dead: Sown in corruption, raised in incorruption;
461Co 15:43 sown in dishonor, raised in glory; sown in weakness, raised in power;
461Co 15:44 sown a natural body, raised a spiritual body. If there is a natural body, there is also a spiritual body.
461Co 15:45 So it is written: The first man Adam became a living being; the last Adam became a life-giving Spirit.
461Co 15:46 However, the spiritual is not first, but the natural; then the spiritual.
461Co 15:47 The first man was from the earth and made of dust; the second man is from heaven.
461Co 15:48 Like the man made of dust, so are those who are made of dust; like the heavenly man, so are those who are heavenly.
461Co 15:49 And just as we have borne the image of the man made of dust, we will also bear the image of the heavenly man.
461Co 15:50 Brothers, I tell you this: flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God, and corruption cannot inherit incorruption.
461Co 15:51 Listen! I am telling you a mystery: We will not all fall asleep, but we will all be changed,
461Co 15:52 in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound, and the dead will be raised incorruptible, and we will be changed.
461Co 15:53 Because this corruptible must be clothed with incorruptibility, and this mortal must be clothed with immortality.
461Co 15:54 Now when this corruptible is clothed with incorruptibility, and this mortal is clothed with immortality, then the saying that is written will take place: Death has been swallowed up in victory.
461Co 15:55 O Death, where is your victory? O Death, where is your sting?
461Co 15:56 Now the sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.
461Co 15:57 But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ!
461Co 15:58 Therefore, my dear brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always excelling in the Lord's work, knowing that your labor in the Lord is not in vain.
461Co 16:1 Now about the collection for the saints: you should do the same as I instructed the Galatian churches.
461Co 16:2 On the first day of the week, each of you is to set something aside and save to the extent that he prospers, so that no collections will need to be made when I come.
461Co 16:3 And when I arrive, I will send those whom you recommend by letter to carry your gracious gift to Jerusalem.
461Co 16:4 If it is also suitable for me to go, they will travel with me.
461Co 16:5 I will come to you after I pass through Macedonia-- for I will be traveling through Macedonia--
461Co 16:6 and perhaps I will remain with you, or even spend the winter, that you may send me on my way wherever I go.
461Co 16:7 I don't want to see you now just in passing, for I hope to spend some time with you, if the Lord allows.
461Co 16:8 But I will stay in Ephesus until Pentecost,
461Co 16:9 because a wide door for effective ministry has opened for me-- yet many oppose me.
461Co 16:10 If Timothy comes, see that he has nothing to fear from you, because he is doing the Lord's work, just as I am.
461Co 16:11 Therefore no one should look down on him; but you should send him on his way in peace so he can come to me, for I am expecting him with the brothers.
461Co 16:12 About our brother Apollos: I strongly urged him to come to you with the brothers, but he was not at all willing to come now. However, when he has time, he will come.
461Co 16:13 Be alert, stand firm in the faith, be brave and strong.
461Co 16:14 Your every [action] must be done with love.
461Co 16:15 Brothers, you know the household of Stephanas: they are the firstfruits of Achaia and have devoted themselves to serving the saints. I urge you
461Co 16:16 also to submit to such people, and to everyone who works and labors with them.
461Co 16:17 I am delighted over the presence of Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus, because these men have made up for your absence.
461Co 16:18 For they have refreshed my spirit and yours. Therefore recognize such people.
461Co 16:19 The churches of the Asian province greet you. Aquila and Priscilla greet you heartily in the Lord, along with the church that meets in their home.
461Co 16:20 All the brothers greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.
461Co 16:21 This greeting is in my own hand-- Paul.
461Co 16:22 If anyone does not love the Lord, a curse be on him. Maranatha!
461Co 16:23 The grace of our Lord Jesus be with you.
461Co 16:24 My love be with all of you in Christ Jesus.
