50Php 1:1 Paul and Timothy, slaves of Christ Jesus: To all the saints in Christ Jesus who are in Philippi, including the overseers and deacons.
50Php 1:2 Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
50Php 1:3 I give thanks to my God for every remembrance of you,
50Php 1:4 always praying with joy for all of you in my every prayer,
50Php 1:5 because of your partnership in the gospel from the first day until now.
50Php 1:6 I am sure of this, that He who started a good work in you will carry it on to completion until the day of Christ Jesus.
50Php 1:7 It is right for me to think this way about all of you, because I have you in my heart, and you are all partners with me in grace, both in my imprisonment and in the defense and establishment of the gospel.
50Php 1:8 For God is my witness, how I deeply miss all of you with the affection of Christ Jesus.
50Php 1:9 And I pray this: that your love will keep on growing in knowledge and every kind of discernment,
50Php 1:10 so that you can determine what really matters and can be pure and blameless in the day of Christ,
50Php 1:11 filled with the fruit of righteousness that [comes] through Jesus Christ, to the glory and praise of God.
50Php 1:12 Now I want you to know, brothers, that what has happened to me has actually resulted in the advancement of the gospel,
50Php 1:13 so that it has become known throughout the whole imperial guard, and to everyone else, that my imprisonment is for Christ.
50Php 1:14 Most of the brothers in the Lord have gained confidence from my imprisonment and dare even more to speak the message fearlessly.
50Php 1:15 Some, to be sure, preach Christ out of envy and strife, but others out of good will.
50Php 1:16 These do so out of love, knowing that I am appointed for the defense of the gospel;
50Php 1:17 the others proclaim Christ out of rivalry, not sincerely, seeking to cause [me] trouble in my imprisonment.
50Php 1:18 What does it matter? Just that in every way, whether out of false motives or true, Christ is proclaimed. And in this I rejoice. Yes, and I will rejoice
50Php 1:19 because I know this will lead to my deliverance through your prayers and help from the Spirit of Jesus Christ.
50Php 1:20 My eager expectation and hope is that I will not be ashamed about anything, but that now as always, with all boldness, Christ will be highly honored in my body, whether by life or by death.
50Php 1:21 For me, living is Christ and dying is gain.
50Php 1:22 Now if I live on in the flesh, this means fruitful work for me; and I don't know which one I should choose.
50Php 1:23 I am pressured by both. I have the desire to depart and be with Christ-- which is far better--
50Php 1:24 but to remain in the flesh is more necessary for you.
50Php 1:25 Since I am persuaded of this, I know that I will remain and continue with all of you for your advancement and joy in the faith,
50Php 1:26 so that, because of me, your confidence may grow in Christ Jesus when I come to you again.
50Php 1:27 Just one thing: live your life in a manner worthy of the gospel of Christ. Then, whether I come and see you or am absent, I will hear about you that you are standing firm in one spirit, with one mind, working side by side for the faith of the gospel,
50Php 1:28 not being frightened in any way by your opponents. This is evidence of their destruction, but of your deliverance-- and this is from God.
50Php 1:29 For it has been given to you on Christ's behalf not only to believe in Him, but also to suffer for Him,
50Php 1:30 having the same struggle that you saw I had and now hear about me.
50Php 2:1 If then there is any encouragement in Christ, if any consolation of love, if any fellowship with the Spirit, if any affection and mercy,
50Php 2:2 fulfill my joy by thinking the same way, having the same love, sharing the same feelings, focusing on one goal.
50Php 2:3 Do nothing out of rivalry or conceit, but in humility consider others as more important than yourselves.
50Php 2:4 Everyone should look out not [only] for his own interests, but also for the interests of others.
50Php 2:5 Make your own attitude that of Christ Jesus,
50Php 2:6 who, existing in the form of God, did not consider equality with God as something to be used for His own advantage.
50Php 2:7 Instead He emptied Himself by assuming the form of a slave, taking on the likeness of men. And when He had come as a man in His external form,
50Php 2:8 He humbled Himself by becoming obedient to the point of death-- even to death on a cross.
50Php 2:9 For this reason God also highly exalted Him and gave Him the name that is above every name,
50Php 2:10 so that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow-- of those who are in heaven and on earth and under the earth--
50Php 2:11 and every tongue should confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.
50Php 2:12 So then, my dear friends, just as you have always obeyed, not only in my presence, but now even more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.
50Php 2:13 For it is God who is working in you, [enabling you] both to will and to act for His good purpose.
50Php 2:14 Do everything without grumbling and arguing,
50Php 2:15 so that you may be blameless and pure, children of God who are faultless in a crooked and perverted generation, among whom you shine like stars in the world.
50Php 2:16 Hold firmly the message of life. Then I can boast in the day of Christ that I didn't run in vain or labor for nothing.
50Php 2:17 But even if I am poured out as a drink offering on the sacrifice and service of your faith, I am glad and rejoice with all of you.
50Php 2:18 In the same way you also should rejoice and share your joy with me.
50Php 2:19 Now I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you soon so that I also may be encouraged when I hear news about you.
50Php 2:20 For I have no one else like-minded who will genuinely care about your interests;
50Php 2:21 all seek their own interests, not those of Jesus Christ.
50Php 2:22 But you know his proven character, because he has served with me in the gospel ministry like a son with a father.
50Php 2:23 Therefore, I hope to send him as soon as I see how things go with me.
50Php 2:24 And I am convinced in the Lord that I myself will also come quickly.
50Php 2:25 But I considered it necessary to send you Epaphroditus-- my brother, co-worker, and fellow soldier, as well as your messenger and minister to my need--
50Php 2:26 since he has been longing for all of you and was distressed because you heard that he was sick.
50Php 2:27 Indeed, he was so sick that he nearly died. However, God had mercy on him, and not only on him but also on me, so that I would not have one grief on top of another.
50Php 2:28 For this reason, I am very eager to send him so that you may rejoice when you see him again and I may be less anxious.
50Php 2:29 Therefore, welcome him in the Lord with all joy and hold men like him in honor,
50Php 2:30 because he came close to death for the work of Christ, risking his life to make up what was lacking in your ministry to me.
50Php 3:1 Finally, my brothers, rejoice in the Lord. To write to you again about this is no trouble for me and is a protection for you.
50Php 3:2 Watch out for "dogs," watch out for evil workers, watch out for those who mutilate the flesh.
50Php 3:3 For we are the circumcision, the ones who serve by the Spirit of God, boast in Christ Jesus, and do not put confidence in the flesh--
50Php 3:4 although I once had confidence in the flesh too. If anyone else thinks he has grounds for confidence in the flesh, I have more:
50Php 3:5 circumcised the eighth day; of the nation of Israel, of the tribe of Benjamin, a Hebrew born of Hebrews; as to the law, a Pharisee;
50Php 3:6 as to zeal, persecuting the church; as to the righteousness that is in the law, blameless.
50Php 3:7 But everything that was a gain to me, I have considered to be a loss because of Christ.
50Php 3:8 More than that, I also consider everything to be a loss in view of the surpassing value of knowing Christ Jesus my Lord. Because of Him I have suffered the loss of all things and consider them filth, so that I may gain Christ
50Php 3:9 and be found in Him, not having a righteousness of my own from the law, but one that is through faith in Christ-- the righteousness from God based on faith.
50Php 3:10 [My goal] is to know Him and the power of His resurrection and the fellowship of His sufferings, being conformed to His death,
50Php 3:11 assuming that I will somehow reach the resurrection from among the dead.
50Php 3:12 Not that I have already reached [the goal] or am already fully mature, but I make every effort to take hold of it because I also have been taken hold of by Christ Jesus.
50Php 3:13 Brothers, I do not consider myself to have taken hold of it. But one thing I do: forgetting what is behind and reaching forward to what is ahead,
50Php 3:14 I pursue as my goal the prize promised by God's heavenly call in Christ Jesus.
50Php 3:15 Therefore, all who are mature should think this way. And if you think differently about anything, God will reveal this to you also.
50Php 3:16 In any case, we should live up to whatever [truth] we have attained.
50Php 3:17 Join in imitating me, brothers, and observe those who live according to the example you have in us.
50Php 3:18 For I have often told you, and now say again with tears, that many live as enemies of the cross of Christ.
50Php 3:19 Their end is destruction; their god is their stomach; their glory is in their shame. They are focused on earthly things,
50Php 3:20 but our citizenship is in heaven, from which we also eagerly wait for a Savior, the Lord Jesus Christ.
50Php 3:21 He will transform the body of our humble condition into the likeness of His glorious body, by the power that enables Him to subject everything to Himself.
50Php 4:1 So then, in this way, my dearly loved brothers, my joy and crown, stand firm in the Lord, dear friends.
50Php 4:2 I urge Euodia and I urge Syntyche to agree in the Lord.
50Php 4:3 Yes, I also ask you, true partner, to help these women who have contended for the gospel at my side, along with Clement and the rest of my co-workers whose names are in the book of life.
50Php 4:4 Rejoice in the Lord always. I will say it again: Rejoice!
50Php 4:5 Let your graciousness be known to everyone. The Lord is near.
50Php 4:6 Don't worry about anything, but in everything, through prayer and petition with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God.
50Php 4:7 And the peace of God, which surpasses every thought, will guard your hearts and your minds in Christ Jesus.
50Php 4:8 Finally brothers, whatever is true, whatever is honorable, whatever is just, whatever is pure, whatever is lovely, whatever is commendable-- if there is any moral excellence and if there is any praise-- dwell on these things.
50Php 4:9 Do what you have learned and received and heard and seen in me, and the God of peace will be with you.
50Php 4:10 I rejoiced in the Lord greatly that now at last you have renewed your care for me. You were, in fact, concerned about me, but lacked the opportunity [to show it].
50Php 4:11 I don't say this out of need, for I have learned to be content in whatever circumstances I am.
50Php 4:12 I know both how to have a little, and I know how to have a lot. In any and all circumstances I have learned the secret [of being content]-- whether well-fed or hungry, whether in abundance or in need.
50Php 4:13 I am able to do all things through Him who strengthens me.
50Php 4:14 Still, you did well by sharing with me in my hardship.
50Php 4:15 And you, Philippians, know that in the early days of the gospel, when I left Macedonia, no church shared with me in the matter of giving and receiving except you alone.
50Php 4:16 For even in Thessalonica you sent [gifts] for my need several times.
50Php 4:17 Not that I seek the gift, but I seek the fruit that is increasing to your account.
50Php 4:18 But I have received everything in full, and I have an abundance. I am fully supplied, having received from Epaphroditus what you provided-- a fragrant offering, a welcome sacrifice, pleasing to God.
50Php 4:19 And my God will supply all your needs according to His riches in glory in Christ Jesus.
50Php 4:20 Now to our God and Father be glory forever and ever. Amen.
50Php 4:21 Greet every saint in Christ Jesus. Those brothers who are with me greet you.
50Php 4:22 All the saints greet you, but especially those from Caesar's household.
50Php 4:23 The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
