57Phm 1:1 Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy, our brother: To Philemon, our dear friend and co-worker,
57Phm 1:2 to Apphia our sister, to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church that meets in your house.
57Phm 1:3 Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
57Phm 1:4 I always thank my God when I mention you in my prayers,
57Phm 1:5 because I hear of your love and faith toward the Lord Jesus and for all the saints.
57Phm 1:6 [I pray] that your participation in the faith may become effective through knowing every good thing that is in us for [the glory of] Christ.
57Phm 1:7 For I have great joy and encouragement from your love, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed through you, brother.
57Phm 1:8 For this reason, although I have great boldness in Christ to command you to do what is right,
57Phm 1:9 I appeal, instead, on the basis of love. I, Paul, as an elderly man and now also as a prisoner of Christ Jesus,
57Phm 1:10 appeal to you for my child, whom I fathered while in chains-- Onesimus.
57Phm 1:11 Once he was useless to you, but now he is useful to both you and me.
57Phm 1:12 I am sending him-- a part of myself-- back to you.
57Phm 1:13 I wanted to keep him with me, so that in my imprisonment for the gospel he might serve me in your place.
57Phm 1:14 But I didn't want to do anything without your consent, so that your good deed might not be out of obligation, but of your own free will.
57Phm 1:15 For perhaps this is why he was separated [from you] for a brief time, so that you might get him back permanently,
57Phm 1:16 no longer as a slave, but more than a slave-- as a dearly loved brother. This is especially so to me, but even more to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.
57Phm 1:17 So if you consider me a partner, accept him as you would me.
57Phm 1:18 And if he has wronged you in any way, or owes you anything, charge that to my account.
57Phm 1:19 I, Paul, write this with my own hand: I will repay it-- not to mention to you that you owe me even your own self.
57Phm 1:20 Yes, brother, may I have joy from you in the Lord; refresh my heart in Christ.
57Phm 1:21 Since I am confident of your obedience, I am writing to you, knowing that you will do even more than I say.
57Phm 1:22 But meanwhile, also prepare a guest room for me, for I hope that through your prayers I will be restored to you.
57Phm 1:23 Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, greets you, and so do
57Phm 1:24 Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my co-workers.
57Phm 1:25 The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
